        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=48767&amp;TOPIC_ID=5955&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Touch+of+Night+vs+Deflux&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         If I have the luxary of having two gems, I usually have both.  Deflux is great for finishing off mobs and for quick bursts of health.  Touch of Night - who cares how much dmg it does. Quite clearly, it's a huge heal to you.  If you have the time and safety, and you're below half health -- it's the route you wanna take.  </P><P>The big thing to remember about the two is cast time. In an emergency situation -- when the root has broken, the fear or darkness has dropped, adds etc -- you want to be able to get health FAST.  You may have less than 1 bub of health.  And Touch of Night has a pretty long cast time. What if it gets interupted?  Deflux is fast.</P><P>So unless I am hunting a zone I am 100% comfortable with / low danger.  I am going to have Deflux memed over Touch of Night.</P><P></P><P>-Smartweed Jackson, 60 Warlock, Druzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
