        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=48770&amp;TOPIC_ID=5955&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Touch+of+Night+vs+Deflux&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         ToN is a nuke spell, plain and simple.  On a raid or a group situation where DoTs aren't efficient (e.g. a fast battle) that's when it really comes into use, because you want to pump out as much damage as possible and ToN is better than Deflux at that.</P><P>But as a method of regaining health? I'd rather stick to Vex or BoD, and use Deflux for emergencies.  Both (Vex & Bod I mean) are more efficient than ToN in terms of damage / mana ratio, and being DoTs, they allow for a more flexible period of healing and won't break root if you're root & doting.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
